{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create a ten-year interest free loan for domestic green energy transition",
        "additional_details": "We believe the current energy sector model is creating misery for millions and wrecking any hope of a decent future for future generations. Alternatives exist now to help tackle many of our problems regarding the climate, cost of living and long-term energy security.\r\n\r\nThis is a critical moment to incentivise people to transition. In the same time it will take to get new nuclear up and running we could reduce peoples' energy costs, massively boost UK-based industry and get a lot closer to meeting our net zero targets.",
        "background": "The Government should create funding in the form of an interest-free loan repayable over (up to) ten years for people to spend on solar, heat pump or insulation projects as appropriate to their domestic situation (including community energy proposals).",
